                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the protagonists and other
                           characters like Gabrǝʾel (fols. 10va, 72va); name of the donor (only the
                           second component or a few letters of it); the word salām “salutation” in
                           Text II; elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 
 Several groups of lines on the
                           incipit page of Texts I-1 and I-4, alternating with black lines; a few
                           lines in the incipit of Text I-2; two initial lines of Texts I-3, II and
                           III; initial line of Text I-5; two initial lines of the sections of Texts
                           I-1 (hymns), I-4, II and III (miracles), partly section numbers of Text
                           I-4; initial line or word of each stanza of Text I-5.</seg>
                     </handNote>
