                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#9va">f. 9va</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#9va">9va</locus>: ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘወኃበቶ፡ ለደብረ፡ ማርያም፡ ሰውኔ፡
                              ስመ፡ አቡሃ፡ ወልደ፡ እስጢፋኖስ፡ ወስመ፡ እማ፡ ወለተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ወስመ፡ አኃቲሃ፡ …</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note states that the Ms. was donated to the monastery of Dabra
                              Māryām Säwne. It mentions the name of the donor’s family members but
                              does not reveal the name of the female donor. The note is written in
                              the same hand that inserted the name ʿĀmata Māryām into supplication
                              formulas throughout the Ms. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#9vb">f. 9vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Testament of wäy[zä]ro Tʿǝbe Kahsay (?) </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic and sealed with signatures and a
                              fingerprint. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#81ra">f. 81ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Excerpt from the hymn ʾǝsaggǝd la-malakotǝka... “I worship Thy
                              Godhead…”.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Crudely written. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#81rb">f. 81rb</locus>
                           <desc>-va: salām laki Māryām dǝngǝl za-mäʿaza ʾafuki kol … “Salutation to
                              you Virgin Mary, your mouth is of apple fragrance ...” (cp. ChRep
                              n</desc>
                           <locus target="#91">91</locus>).<quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Crudely written. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#84r">f. 84r</locus>
                           <desc>: Unclear note. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic and Tǝgrǝñña (?) and sealed with
                              signatures and two fingerprints. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- <locus target="#83rv">83rv</locus> (included in quire B)
                           contains an excerpt from the Psalter (P<locus from="132" to="133">132-133</locus>), in the main hand.
 - Spaces for rubricated
                           names of the donors are frequently left unfilled: <locus target="#7va">7va</locus>, 11va, 15vb, 19rb etc.
 - Omitted letters or words
                           inserted interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#5va">5va</locus>, 8ra, 8vb,
                           22vb, 33vb, 35ra, 40vb, 44ra, 60vb.
 - Thin black lines for line
                           filling on <locus target="#12va">12va</locus>.
 - Scribbles on <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>.
 - Crude drawings on <locus from="1v" to="2r">1v-2r</locus>.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">In Text I-4, readings are indicated by the names of
                              the feasts, written in the upper margin, in the main hand between
                              dashes: ዘጸዴንያ: <locus target="#18va">fol. 18va</locus> ዘቍስቋም: <locus target="#19rb">fol. 19rb</locus>. In addition, readings are
                              indicated by the names of the feasts and other occasions, crudely
                              written in the upper margin or in lacunae, in pen: fols. 28rb, 28vb,
                              30va, 32ra, 33r, 34va, 38rb, 49rb, 53va, 54ra, 60vb, 63ra, 68vb,
                              70vb</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
